title: Did 2,600 votes were found uncounted in Floyd County, Georgia?
subtitle: It was discovered during a State audit, which is different from the recounting of votes.
author: Jordan Liles
vclaim: Some 2,600 uncounted votes were found. The majority of the votes were cast by President Donald Trump of the United States, in Floyd County, Georgia, bringing the President nearly 800 votes closer to the census of President-elect Joe Biden in the 2020 general election.
